President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. J. Paul Compton Jr. of Alabama is nominated to be General Counsel at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. Robert R. Hood of Georgia is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Defense, Legislative Affairs. David S. Jonas of Pennsylvania is nominated to be General Counsel at the Department of Energy. George Nesterczuk of Virginia is nominated to be Director of the Office of Personnel Management. These individuals have diverse backgrounds and experience in law, government affairs, and management consulting.